-- PRESS DIGEST - Bulgaria - Oct 9
-- 
-- Thu Oct 09, 2014 03:05AM EDT
-- None



SOFIA, Oct 9 (Reuters) - These are some of the main stories in Bulgarian newspapers on Thursday. Reuters has not verified these stories and does not vouch for their accuracy.

-- Bulgarian state energy regulator mulls introducing a new fee in the sector which will be applicable to all power generators, regulator chair Svetla Todorova said (Trud, Standart, Sega, Presa, Monitor, Capital daily, Duma, 24 Chasa). -- The number of EU tourists in Bulgaria dropped 15.5 percent in the first eight months of the year on an annual basis, the Association of tour operators and tour agencies' data showed (Trud, Standart, Sega, Presa, Monitor, 24 Chasa). -- French actor Gerard Depardieu will shoot a film, with working title Le Voyage, in Bulgaria. The shoot starts in November in the village of Kaloyanovo, near the southern city of Plovdiv (24 Chasa, Standart). -- Archaeologists have uncovered a unique medallion with spiralled snake heads in an excavation at the Kastra Rubra fortress, near the southern town of Harmanli.